Why Maven?
-----------
- TestNG XML files cannot be executed directly outside the IDE.
- Maven is a Build Tool used to build and execute the project from the command line.
- Maven uses pom.xml as the central configuration file.

pom.xml Contains:
-----------------
1. Dependencies
   - Required libraries for the project.
   - Example: Selenium, TestNG, Apache POI, Log4j, etc.

2. Plugins
   - Used to perform build-related activities.

Important Maven Plugins:
------------------------

1. Maven Compiler Plugin
   - Compiles Java source code.
   - Converts .java files into .class files.

2. Maven Surefire Plugin
   - Executes TestNG/JUnit test cases.
   - Runs the TestNG XML file specified in pom.xml.

Example:

<plugin>
    <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
    <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>3.2.2</version>
    <configuration>
        <suiteXmlFiles>
            <suiteXmlFile>master.xml</suiteXmlFile>
        </suiteXmlFiles>
    </configuration>
</plugin>

Note:
- Any TestNG XML file can be executed by specifying it inside
  <suiteXmlFile> tag.

