mvn test:
---------

Command:

mvn test

Lifecycle Executed:

validate
    ↓
compile
    ↓
test

Step 1: validate
- Validates project structure.
- Checks pom.xml.

Step 2: compile
- Compiles source code from src/main/java.
- Generates .class files.

Step 3: test
- Compiles test code from src/test/java.
- Executes TestNG/JUnit test cases using Surefire Plugin.

Results:

Case 1 - All Tests Pass

Tests run: 10
Failures: 0
Errors: 0
Skipped: 0

BUILD SUCCESS

Case 2 - Any Test Fails

Tests run: 10
Failures: 2
Errors: 0
Skipped: 0

BUILD FAILURE

Important Point:
- Even one failed test case will result in BUILD FAILURE.
- All test cases must pass to get BUILD SUCCESS.

Interview Answer:

mvn test executes the Validate → Compile → Test phases of the
Maven lifecycle. It compiles application code, compiles test
code, and executes TestNG/JUnit test cases. If all tests pass,
Maven shows BUILD SUCCESS; otherwise BUILD FAILURE.

